    "title": "Verb (क्रिया/क्रियापद)",
    "description": "Definition, Forms of Verbs (V1, V2, V3), Confusing Verbs and Special Adjective Forms.",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "Introduction to Verb (परिचय)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "A **Verb** is a word used to describe an action, state, or occurrence. It is the most important part of a sentence.<br/>जो शब्द किसी कार्य, स्थिति या घटना को दर्शाता है, उसे **क्रिया (Verb)** कहते हैं।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Action Verbs:** Run (दौड़ना), Play (खेलना), Eat (खाना), Write (लिखना)",
                        "**State Verbs:** Is, Am, Are, Was, Were, Have, Has"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "Forms of Verbs (क्रिया के रूप)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "note",
                    "content": "There are three main forms of verbs:<br/>1. **Base Form (V1)** - मूल रूप<br/>2. **Past Form (V2)** - भूतकाल<br/>3. **Past Participle (V3)** - भूतकालिक कृदंत"
